column61: Fairly large swell from previous days storm. Array deployed. Lvg. Station 90.28

Lvg. Station: 93.30. Array deployed. Wind: 10-15 knts. Ship speed: 8.5 knts.
Excused from drills by chief scientist.
Off transect line to investigate "rescue" flares off port bow: Was Navy excersise.
Lvng: 93.35. Array deployed. Glare: 10:00 to 14:00 ahead.
Lvg: 93.55. Light haze on the horizon.
Conducting Off Effort obs as ship is off of trackline steaming to station 93.60.
Ship returning to San Diego for repairs. Towing array/conducting Off Effort obs on run in.
Stopped off effort obs as crew spraying rust inhibitor everywhere.
Ship steaming to 93.70. Conducting Off Effort obs as ship is not on trackline.
Clouds moving in. Winds 10-15 kts. Ship speed: 9.6 kts.
Lvng station: 93.80. Ship speed: 9.5 kts. Data recreated
Lvng station: 93.100. Array deployed. Winds: NW 10-15 kts. Ship speed: 9.7 kts.
Observed thru big eyes for twenty minutes, no animals observed.
Array deployed. Ship speed: 9.2 kts. Winds: W/NW 5-15 kts.

Array deployed. Ship speed: 9.1 kts. Winds: 2-4 kts.
Winds building: NW 15-20 kts. Seas building.

Winds: 27-35 kts. Sea state worsening. Ship speed: 9.1 kts.

Array deployed. Winds: W/NW 10-20 kts. Ship speed: 9.6 kts. Glare: 2130-2330.

Winds:  NW 25-30 kts. Ship speed: 8.3 kts.

Winds: W/NW 10-15 kts. Ship speed: 9.6 kts.
